:::


The `dm` dataset contains CDISC-standard demographic variables: `SUBJID`, `AGE`, `SEX`, `RACE`, `ARMCD` (arm code), `ARM` (arm label).

Now, generate a Table 14.1.1 using **gtsummary**:


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
# Filter to ITT population (assuming all randomized subjects are in ITT)
demographics_table <- dm %>%
  filter(ARM != "Screen Failure") %>%
  select(USUBJID, ARM, AGE, SEX, RACE) %>%
  tbl_summary(
    by = ARM,
    label = list(
      AGE ~ "Age (years)",
      SEX ~ "Sex",
      RACE ~ "Race"
    ),
    type = list(
      AGE ~ "continuous",
      SEX ~ "categorical",
      RACE ~ "categorical"
    ),
    statistic = list(
      all_continuous() ~ "{mean} ({sd})",
      all_categorical() ~ "{n} ({p}%)"
    )
  ) %>%
  add_overall() %>%
  modify_header(label = "Characteristic") %>%
  modify_caption("**Table 14.1.1:** Demographics and Baseline Characteristics – Intent-to-Treat Population")

# Display: HTML format shows interactive table, other formats use kable
if (knitr::pandoc_to() %in% c("html", "html4", "html5")) {
  demographics_table
} else {
  demographics_table %>% as_kable()
}
```

