### 20.5.4 Example 3: Listing of Serious Adverse Events

Listings are detailed, row-level presentations. Here's a listing of all Serious Adverse Events (SAEs):


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
# Filter to SAEs only
saes <- ae %>%
  filter(AESER == "Y") %>%
  left_join(dm %>% filter(ARM != "Screen Failure") %>% select(USUBJID, ARM), by = "USUBJID") %>%
  filter(!is.na(ARM)) %>%
  select(USUBJID, ARM, AESOC, AETERM, AESEV, AEONSET = AESTDTC, AEOFFSET = AEENDTC, AEACN) %>%
  arrange(ARM, USUBJID, AEONSET)

if (knitr::pandoc_to() %in% c("html", "html4", "html5")) {
  sae_listing <- flextable(saes) %>%
    set_header_labels(
      USUBJID = "Subject ID", ARM = "Treatment Arm", AESOC = "System Organ Class",
      AETERM = "Preferred Term", AESEV = "Severity",
      AEONSET = "Onset Date", AEOFFSET = "Offset Date", AEACN = "Action Taken"
    ) %>%
    theme_booktabs() %>% autofit() %>%
    add_header_row(values = "Listing of Serious Adverse Events – Safety Population",
                   colwidths = 8) %>%
    bold(part = "header")
  sae_listing
} else {
  knitr::kable(head(saes, 20), caption = "Listing of Serious Adverse Events (first 20 rows)")
}
```

